  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: In group chat there are 2 users: Hudson and Watson. You sent 0.7 ether to Hudson. Than paste new command `/send Watson 0.013`. As a result, screen with fee will be shown and previous sum used: \"0.7\". If do not change anything and send it then Unsigned transaction screen will show expected amount \"0.013\" but wrong recipient: Hudson. If send the transaction then Hudson will receive 0.013 ETH. \r\nExpected: command and its parameters can be typed or copy/pasted and used.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n![img_0512](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/28383420-62644a5a-6cc1-11e7-91bc-80fd5ea35d48.jpg)\r\n![img_0513](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/28383426-66238b10-6cc1-11e7-8b86-d19ab4f8c99f.jpg)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\ncan paste valid command and send it\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nif paste `/send Watson 0.013` then recipient from previous send command is used instead of valid specified \"Watson\"\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nvideo: https://drive.google.com/open?id=0Bz3t9zSg1wb7eUp3dUd5YXJ5dmc\r\n- copy command `/send Watson 0.013`\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open group chat with Hudson and Watson\r\n- send to Hudson 0.000007777 eth and confirm transaction\r\n- after returning to group chat: paste `/send Watson 0.013` and send it without modifications. Check sum shown on fee screen and recipient on Unsigned transactions screen\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: develop 0.9.8-85-gcad5e0c5+\r\n* Operating System: \r\nReal device Samsung Galaxy S6, Android 6.0.1\r\nReal device iPhone 6s, iOS 10.2.1\r\n",
